  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Myanmar Population Movement</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">October-December 2016: An initial influx of people from Rakhine State in Myanmar to Cox s Bazar takes place with some 87 000 arrivals recorded. These population movements are not a new event in this area. Historically some Muslim communities from Rakhine have been migrating to Bangladesh over the past three decades where they live as either refugees or without status. 25 August 2017: Violence in Myanmar s state of Rakhine prompts aninflux of people into South East Bangladesh. As of 19 September 2017 the Inter Sector Coordination Group (ISCG) reported that an estimated 422 000 people have crossed the border into Bangladesh. This page is specific to response on the Myanmar side of the border.</narrative>
  </description>
